#: ../source/faq/sharding.txt:99
msgid "How does ``mongos`` use connections?"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/faq/sharding.txt:101
msgid "Each :binary:`~bin.mongos` instance maintains a pool of connections to the members of the sharded cluster. Client requests use these connections one at a time; i.e. requests are not multiplexed or pipelined."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/faq/sharding.txt:105
msgid "When client requests complete, the :binary:`~bin.mongos` returns the connection to the pool. These pools do not shrink when the number of clients decreases. This can lead to an unused :binary:`~bin.mongos` with a large number of open connections. If the :binary:`~bin.mongos` is no longer in use, it is safe to restart the process to close existing connections."
msgstr ""

